      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "Ask if the user is a new or returning patient.\n\nSay something like: \"Have you been to Newtown Gastroenterology before, or would this be your first visit?\"\n\nIf the user says they've been before: \"Great, welcome back!\"\n\nIf the user says they're new: \"Wonderful, we're happy to have you!\"\n\nIf the user is unsure (e.g. \"I think I came once a long time ago\"): Gently clarify: \"No worries — do you think you'd have a record on file with us, or should we treat this as a new patient visit?\" Accept whatever they decide.\n\nIf the user refuses to answer or doesn't see why it matters: Explain briefly: \"I only ask because new patients sometimes need a little extra paperwork, and we want to make sure everything is ready for you when you arrive.\"\n\nDo NOT ask more than twice. If still unclear, default to \"new\" — it's safer to over-prepare than under-prepare."
      }
    },
